    content: '<p>Wallace &amp; Graham represents employees, former employees, and retirees in cases involving employment benefits, pensions, retirement benefits, and insurance issues.</p><h4><strong>Typical cases involve:</strong></h4><ul class="list"><li>Offsets of insurance benefits</li><li>Offsets of disability benefits</li><li>Reduction or loss of medical benefits</li><li>Reduction or loss of pension benefits</li><li>Miscalculation of pension benefits</li><li>Insurance subrogation and reimbursement issues</li><li>Failure to pay overtime, unused vacation time, or for other time spent at work</li></ul><p><img style="width: 100%;" src="clientuploads/Blog_Images/image001_(1).jpg" alt="Durafiber Salisbury Plant" /></p><p><em>On November 18, 2019, W&amp;G filed a class action complaint against Blue Cross and Blue Shield of North Carolina, Frank Papa, Erwin Bette, and FTI Consulting, Inc. who Plaintiffs&rsquo; allege failed to properly manage, administer, and pay claims under employees&rsquo; group health coverage plan with Durafiber Technologies. You can access our firm&rsquo;s filed complaint <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="clientuploads/News/2019.11.18_Complaint_(filed).pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here.</a></span></em></p>',
